description:
Available at: https://openstudionetwork.com/keezer - These lessons will help bring a stronger rhythmic element to your playing. Geoffrey teaches you to "think like a drummer" by practicing actual drum patterns on the piano keyboard, as well as developing finger independence and fluidity alternating between eighth notes, sixteenth notes and triplets.  

Includes:

• Paradiddles
• Double Paradiddles
• Triple Paradiddles
• Alternating 8th notes and Triplets
• Alternating 16th notes and Triplets
• Triplets in Groups of Four
• Developing Finger Independence **
• Rhythmic Independence **
• PDF's

Level: Intermediate/Advanced
title: Geoffrey Keezer - Rhythm (Preview)
